news.title: Ludhiana: Developers who did not pay dues can't sell, buy properties
news.para: The civic body has to recover around Rs 13 crore from the defaulters and it has written against 27 of them in Zone D, while for the other zones the process is on.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP inspects CHD Avenue 71 as residents say infra work incomplete
news.para: On July 26, the residents filed a complaint against the developer on CM window alleging several deficiencies in the project.

news.title: Gurugram: DHBVN stops new power connections as 16 builders fail to pay Rs 317 crore dues
news.para: Around 40,000 people live in these areas. According to DHBVN officials, the developers of these residential colonies have failed to set up around 20 substations for power supply.

news.title: Supertech case: Probe reveals Noida authority formed panel to clear building plans
news.para: The seven officials, five of whom are now retired, named in Noida Authority’s report that has been sent to the state government were all part of this committee.

news.title: Supertech twin tower case: SIT begins probe, asks for old Noida files and records
news.para: While that investigation is on, Noida officials will soon begin talks with officials at the CBRI to coordinate on preparations to bring down the twin towers, which SC ordered demolished earlier this week. The court had directed Noida to consult CBRI for the demolition.

news.title: Gurugram: Ambience Mall owner booked for Rs 289 crore fraud
news.para: Apart from Gehlot, CBI has also charged other directors of his firm, Aman Hospitality Pvt Ltd, and yet to be identified bank officials with conspiring to defraud the bank.

news.title: Lavasa residents count on final bid decision for pending project
news.para: Residents said that Mumbai-based Darwin Group of companies and Delhi-based Dhir and Dhir Associates have submitted their bid and are now hoping that the CoCs weigh the ability of the resolution applicant thoroughly in the interest of the residents, who have been waiting for the last three years for the final decision.

news.title: SC asks Amrapali buyers to clear dues, warns failure may result in flats' cancellation
news.para: A special bench of Justice U U Lalit and Ajay Rastogi observed that the home buyers are under the impression that the court is facilitating construction of their stalled flats and managing funds and they are at a convenience to pay their dues, whenever they like.

news.title: Evergrande: China's fragile housing giant
news.para: Any possible bankruptcy of the group -- which claims to employ 200,000 people and indirectly generate 3.8 million jobs in China -- would have major repercussions on the country's economy, and possibly the world.

news.title: Ireland announces multibillion euro plan to fix housing crisis
news.para: The plan, which includes a guarantee of 20 billion euros ($24 billion) of state funding over the first five years, is aimed at increasing homebuilding to an average of 33,000 units per year by 2030 from around 20,000 last year.

news.title: New Zealand's central bank seeks tougher mortgage rules ahead of rate decision
news.para: Investors have continued to buy properties, buoyed by historically low interest rates and cheap access to finance from the government's pandemic stimulus spending.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body launches single-window TDR clearance for heritage homes
news.para: The committee was also informed that 13 listed heritage buildings have been demolished while 230 heritage homes are yet to tagged with special heritage plates.

news.title: Greater Noida authority imposes fine on four builders for violating NGT norms
news.para: A penalty of Rs 50,000 was levied on Anand Builder and Moni Construction Company. A fine of Rs 1 lakh was imposed on the Apex Alphabet and French Apartments.

news.title: Kolhapur: Construction at Bramhapuri hill without ASI permission
news.para: Social activists from the Bhrashtachar Virodhi Janshakti party have written to Ravikant Adsul, the deputy commissioner of Kolhapur Municipal Corporation, to stop the construction activities immediately.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: New bill allows registrars to cancel a forged property document
news.para: ​​According to the State Amendment Bill to the Registration Act, 1908, (a Central legislation), a registering officer shall refuse to register a forged document.
